any advice on making a new career choice i have been in the army for the last years i got out of the army to take care of my grandfather which i am still doing i have a month old son i have the g i bill for school but i am so unsure of what to do i was a cargo specialist for years and a health care specialist for years so i have already changed my career path twice i have no idea what i would be content with long term any help would be appreciated barbara sher is a wonderful author that helps people find what they are passionate about and create a career around that she has written many books but my favorite is her first book wishcraft which is available free to download online at www wishcraft com in it she asks questions like what would you do if you had all the resources you needed to do it education money etc and were guaranteed to be successful at it what would your ideal day look like what time would you get up what kind of clothes would you put on where would you go what kind of people would you interact with etc what section of the bookstore do you like to go to what section of the newspaper do you like to read first i believe we were given passions for a reason and the world needs us to live those out by doing so we will be living our life purpose and be fulfilled as well listen to your heart often clues are back in our childhood as to what kind of dreams we had what we liked to do what kind of people we were drawn to etc once a person identifies their passion fear often blocks them pursuing it to deal with that i recommend 'feel the fear and do it anyway' by susan jeffers all the best in finding and living your passion A Course In Miracles The Dalek Invasion of Earth Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Homeschooling CPU cache Nicomachean Ethics God Emperor of Dune Theory of conduct Current teachings of Prem Rawat Love Wheel of Fortune Psychoanalysis Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Economics Human sexual behavior Emperor Xu